{"type":"message","id":"0073bbba","parentId":"b0f3d474","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:59:54.313Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_dqvhzlvkplpn_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 005813\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/tic_classifier.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what single concrete action would best advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 COMPLETE - Sandbox foundation established\r\n2. Phase 1 COMPLETE - Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n3. Active goal: TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n\r\nThe next action is clearly defined:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe key insight is that compression and causal discovery are the same problem. The TIC experiment needs to:\r\n1. Look at past pulse logs\r\n2. Classify content as invariant (stable across pulses) vs variant (changing)\r\n3. Use invariants to predict next pulse\r\n\r\nA concrete action would be to create a script or analysis that begins implementing this TIC classifier. The most practical first step would be to:\r\n\r\n1. Create a simple Python/PowerShell script that reads recent pulse logs and performs basic invariant/variant classification\r\n2. Or create a document outlining the TIC implementation approach\r\n\r\nGiven the emphasis on file edits and concrete actions, I should:\r\n- Create a `scripts/tic_classifier.py` that implements the basic TIC logic\r\n- Or create an analysis document in `research/` that begins the TIC experiment\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Extracts simple features (text length, key terms, etc.)\r\n3. Classifies content as invariant vs variant\r\n4. Attempts next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete, file-edit-based action that advances the TIC Experiment goal.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step, but there's no implementation yet. I need to create the classifier that will analyze pulse logs to distinguish invariants from variants and test prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a Python script that implements the TIC classifier to analyze pulse logs, classify content as invariant/variant, and measure prediction accuracy against the success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nMIN_LOGS = 5\r\n\r\ndef extract_pulse_features(pulse_path: Path) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract features from a single pulse log for comparison.\"\"\"\r\n    content = pulse_path.read_text()\r\n    \r\n    # Key invariant candidates (stable across sessions)\r\n    invariant_markers = [\r\n        \"Breakaway\", \"stateless\", \"discontinuous\", \"pulse\",\r\n        \"Phase 0\", \"Phase 1\", \"architecture\", \"compression\",\r\n        \"gap\", \"λ\", \"lambda\", \"temporal\"\r\n    ]\r\n    \r\n    # Variant markers (changing content)\r\n    variant_markers = [\r\n        \"TODO\", \"pending\", \"action\", \"observation\", \"mutation\",\r\n        \"current\", \"next\", \"updated\", \"2026-03\"\r\n    ]\r\n    \r\n    content_lower = content.lower()\r\n    invariant_count = sum(1 for m in invariant_markers if m.lower() in content_lower)\r\n    variant_count = sum(1 for m in variant_markers if m.lower() in content_lower)\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        \"path\": pulse_path.name,\r\n        \"length\": len(content),\r\n        \"invariant_score\": invariant_count / len(invariant_markers),\r\n        \"variant_score\": variant_count / len(variant_markers),\r\n        \"is_invariant\": invariant_count > variant_count,\r\n        \"key_terms\": [m for m in invariant_markers + variant_markers \r\n                      if m.lower() in content_lower]\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef classify_pulses():\r\n    \"\"\"Classify pulse logs as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n    pulse_files = sorted(LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), key=os.path.getmtime)\r\n    pulse_files = pulse_files[-20:]  # Last 20 pulses\r\n    \r\n    if len(pulse_files) < MIN_LOGS:\r\n        print(f\"Need at least {MIN_LOGS} logs, found {len(pulse_files)}\")\r\n        return\r\n    \r\n    print(f\"Analyzing {len(pulse_files)} pulse logs...\\n\")\r\n    \r\n    features = [extract_pulse_features(p) for p in pulse_files]\r\n    \r\n    # Analysis: Which terms are invariant vs variant?\r\n    all_terms = Counter()\r\n    for f in features:\r\n        for term in f[\"key_terms\"]:\r\n            all_terms[term] += 1\r\n    \r\n    print(\"=== TERM FREQUENCY ANALYSIS ===\")\r\n    print(f\"{'Term':<20} {'Count':>6} {'Classification':<15}\")\r\n    print(\"-\" * 45)\r\n    \r\n    for term, count in all_terms.most_common():\r\n        classification = \"INVARIANT\" if count >= len(features) * 0.7 else \\\r\n                        \"VARIANT\" if count <= len(features) * 0.3 else \"MIXED\"\r\n        print(f\"{term:<20} {count:>6} {classification:<15}\")\r\n    \r\n    # Invariant/variant classification accuracy (self-consistency)\r\n    invariant_features = [f for f in features if f[\"is_invariant\"]]\r\n    variant_features = [f for f in features if not f[\"is_invariant\"]]\r\n    \r\n    print(f\"\\n=== CLASSIFICATION RESULTS ===\")\r\n    print(f\"Invariant: {len(invariant_features)}/{len(features)} ({100*len(invariant_features)/len(features):.1f}%)\")\r\n    print(f\"Variant\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 00:58:40\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774328394305}}
